HEADWORD: Outcome
<hw>Out"come</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which comes out
of, or follows from, something else; issue; result; consequence;
upshot.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The logical <xex>outcome</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>H.
Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All true literature, all genuine poetry, is the direct
<qex>outcome</qex>, the condensed essence, of actual life and
thought.</q> <rj><qau>J. C. Shairp.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outcompass</ent>⟦br⟧
